    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You can see [here](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/master/pandas/core/frame.py#L3262) that `sort_values` treats the case where `length(by)` is greater than one differently than when it's equal to one. When you pass a list of columns to sort by, it has to go through our factorization routines, which requires hashable values."
