    "created_at": "2019-02-13T17:46:34Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-02-13T17:46:34Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`sort_values` needs the values of a column to be hashable when sorting by multiple columns. The original example could be fixed by converting the column of (unhashable) lists to a column of tuples.\r\n\r\n\r\n```python\r\nIn [10]: df['fun2'] = df['fun'].map(tuple)\r\n\r\nIn [11]: df\r\nOut[11]:\r\n   a       b                 fun                fun2\r\n0  1  Python  [P, y, t, h, o, n]  (P, y, t, h, o, n)\r\n1  2    Java        [J, a, v, a]        (J, a, v, a)\r\n\r\nIn [12]: df.sort_values(['a', 'fun2'])\r\nOut[12]:\r\n   a       b                 fun                fun2\r\n0  1  Python  [P, y, t, h, o, n]  (P, y, t, h, o, n)\r\n1  2    Java        [J, a, v, a]        (J, a, v, a)\r\n``` "
  },
